subSubSection.paragraph:
Euseius finlandicus
has been reported in orchards and grapevines in various countries in Europe. This species is widespread, mainly in the Palaearctic region. It feeds on
P ulmi
and various eriophyid mites. It is a type IV predatory mite with its highest reproductive capacity reached when feeding on pollen ( McMurtry and Croft 1997 ; Broufas and Koveos 2000;
McMurtry et al. 2013
).

This species was already known from Slovenia ( Miklavc 2006 ; Bohinc and Trdan 2013 ;
Bohinc et al. 2018
). With 375 specimens in total in 21 locations, it is one of the more common and widespread in that survey.
